    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Barbie Question</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David Hawkins letter wonders if Barbie for President doll will encourage girls to run for president, or discourage them (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A May 4 letter writer says that ''if merely owning a President Barbie inspires in just a small percentage of the millions of girls who will doubtless own this doll the desire to run for president, maybe it's not such a terrible thing.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A May 4 letter writer says that ''if merely owning a President Barbie inspires in just a small percentage of the millions of girls who will doubtless own this doll the desire to run for president, maybe it's not such a terrible thing.''</p>
        <p>How about if it discourages a large percentage?</p>
        <p>DAVID HAWKINS  Brooklyn, May 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
